The paper deals with image restoration problems such as deblurring, inpainting, and compressive sensing recovery, which are all related to computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves the use of a non-convex optimization framework, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and machine learning (cs.LG). The method also involves the use of the nuclear norm, which is a common tool in matrix completion and low-rank matrix recovery (cs.MM). Finally, the paper discusses the perceptual quality of the restored images, which is related to subjective image quality assessment (cs.SI).
